9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 460, L.D. 721, “Resolve, to Support the
10 Full Implementation of Certified Community Behavioral Health Clinics in the State”
11 Amend the resolve in the emergency preamble in the 4th paragraph in the last line (page
12 1, line 10 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "State" the following: 'by the
13 implementation deadline'
14 Amend the resolve by striking out everything after the emergency preamble and before
15 the emergency clause and inserting the following:
16 'Sec. 1. Appropriations and allocations. Resolved: That the following
17 appropriations and allocations are made.
18 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES, DEPARTMENT OF
19 Medical Care - Payments to Providers 0147
20 Initiative: Provides one-time funding to support the full implementation of the 5 certified
21 community behavioral health clinics certified by the State as part of the federal Certified
22 Community Behavioral Health Clinic Medicaid Demonstration Program under the United
23 States Department of Health and Human Services, Centers for Medicare and Medicaid
24 Services, including hiring clinical and administrative staff critical to the success of the
25 program. The funding must support enhancement of the department's certified community
26 behavioral health clinics in a manner that enables the department to access the designated
27 enhanced federal match for the program. The department must continue to engage with
28 certified community behavioral health clinic providers regarding how available funding is
29 best leveraged for the program to achieve full implementation.
